# Appointment Workflow Overhaul — Implementation Plan

## Bug Fix 1: Double-Booking False Positives

**Root cause:** [findExistingAppointment()](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart#207-222) in [appointment_service.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart) queries by `patient_phone` + [doctor](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/scripts/setup_pocketbase.dart#112-131) + `status=scheduled`, but it matches **any** scheduled appointment for that phone — even when a different patient has a cancelled slot at that time and a new patient is being booked. The check is phone-based, not patient-identity-based.

**Scenario 1:** Patient A at 5:00 PM is cancelled → Patient B is booked at 5:00 PM → Warning says "existing appointment" because Patient A's `patient_phone` may match if the same phone was used. Actually, the real issue is the filter doesn't account for cancelled appointments properly, AND it runs the check without a date filter, so it matches ANY future scheduled appointment for that phone across all dates.

### Fix

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_service.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart)
- Update [findExistingAppointment()](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart#207-222) to also filter by `status != "cancelled"` explicitly, and only match status `"scheduled"` or `"in_progress"` (skip completed/cancelled)
- This is already done (`status = "scheduled"`), but the real fix is to pass the **date** from [create_appointment_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/create_appointment_screen.dart) so it only checks the same date

#### [MODIFY] [create_appointment_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/create_appointment_screen.dart)
- Pass the selected date when calling [findExistingAppointment(phone, doctorId, date: selectedDate)](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart#207-222) so it only flags true same-date conflicts

---

## Bug Fix 2: Appointment Ending Prematurely

**Root cause:** In [patient_info_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/patient_info_screen.dart), [_submit()](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/consultations/screens/consultation_screen.dart#201-286) calls [linkPatient()](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart#95-108) which sets status to `in_progress`. When the card refreshes, it sees `isInProgress && hasPatientLinked` → shows **"Appointment Ended"** button. The user is seeing the button label and reading it as if the appointment ended.

The actual problem: after filling patient details, the card immediately shows an "Appointment Ended" button. Per user's request, this should be **"Start Consultation"** instead.

### New Appointment Lifecycle

```
Scheduled → Patient Arrived (in_progress) → Fill Details → Start Consultation → [Consultation Form] → Appointment Ended
```

---

## Feature: Start Consultation Flow

### [MODIFY] [appointment_list_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart)

Replace the current **"Appointment Ended"** button (shown when `isInProgress && hasPatientLinked`) with **"Start Consultation"**:

- **"Start Consultation"** button: Checks for existing ongoing consultation for that patient → if none, creates one and navigates to [ConsultationScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/consultations/screens/consultation_screen.dart#16-35) → if one exists, navigates directly to it
- Record `consultation_start_time` on the appointment when starting
- **"Appointment Ended"** button: Only shows after consultation is completed (status check)
- Record `check_out_time` when ended

Add a new `_startConsultation(AppointmentModel apt)` method that:
1. Checks if patient has an ongoing consultation via PocketBase
2. If yes → navigate to it
3. If no → create a new consultation record, navigate to [ConsultationScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/consultations/screens/consultation_screen.dart#16-35)

### [MODIFY] [appointment_service.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart)

- Add `findOngoingConsultation(String patientId, String doctorId)` method
- Add [createConsultation(String patientId, String doctorId)](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/treatment_service.dart#15-77) method (creates with `ongoing` status)

### [MODIFY] [appointment_model.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/models/appointment_model.dart)

- Add optional `consultationStartTime` field (to track when consultation was started)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This requires a `consultation_start_time` field in the PocketBase [appointments](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/scripts/setup_pocketbase.dart#149-164) collection. The user will need to add this field manually in the PocketBase admin, OR we can handle it gracefully by storing the time in the consultation record's `created` timestamp instead.

### Consultation Time Tracking

The consultation start time = when "Start Consultation" is clicked (stored in `ConsultationModel.created`)
The consultation end time = when the consultation form is saved/completed (the `updated` timestamp or a new `completed_at` field)

### Session Start/End in Schedule

> [!NOTE]
> Session cards already appear in the schedule. The requested "Start Session" button + time tracking is a future enhancement that builds on this workflow. For now, focusing on the consultation flow integration.

